name: Golden-Delicious
title: Apple Golden Delicious Class 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 180g Description: Golden Delicious has a white juicy pulp and a greenish yellow shell. The taste is mellow and sweet; making Golden Delicious suitable for desserts.

name: Granny-Smith
title: Apple Granny Smith Class 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 180g Description: Granny Smith is a green apple with white; firm pulp and a clear acidity in the flavor.

name: Pink-Lady
title: Apple Pink Lady Klass 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 180g Description: Pink Lady reminds of Royal Gala; though it is an even sweeter and crispier apple.

name: Red-Delicious
title: Apple Red Delicious Klass 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 160g Description: Red Delicious is a dark red apple with relatively soft pulp and sweet taste.

name: Royal-Gala
title: Apple Royal Gala Klass 1
description: Country and volume: Argentina; ca 180g Description: Royal Gala is a crispy and very juicy apple; with yellow-white pulp. The peel is thin with a red yellow speckled color.

name: Avocado
title: Avocado Class 1
description: Country: Peru Description: Avocado is a fruit with a clear core in the middle. The pulp is light yellow and the peel may vary from light green to dark green; almost black. Avocado fits for starters; salads and as an ingredient in Guacamole.s

name: Banana
title: Banana Ecological Class 1
description: Country and volume: Ecuador; ca 180g Description: An ecologically grown banana. Bananas are good as snacks. The banana is temperature sensitive; very sensitive to dehydration; ethylene and cold damage. Store in room temperature or cool; never in a refrigerator.

name: Kiwi
title: Kiwi Class 1
description: Country: Italy Description: Kiwi; or Chinese currants; as it is also called; has a sweet taste with clear acidity. The fruit is rich in vitamin C.

name: Lemon
title: Lemon Class 1
description: Country: Spain Description: Lemon is used as a flavor in food and drinks and has a very tart and sour taste.

name: Lime
title: Lime Class 1
description: Country: Brazil Description: The lime fruit; like lemon; has sour taste; with the difference that the lime is more juicy and flavorsome than the lemon. It is mainly the juice you use but also the shell can be used.

name: Mango
title: Mango Class 1
description: Country: Mexico Description: Mango has a fresh; powerful and sweet taste; but a special exotic shade. Inside there is a large; oval kernel in which the pulp is grown in. This makes the best way to cut mango is with the shell on. Divide the fruit by cutting along on both sides of the core. Mango can be eaten naturally or in desserts; entrees and main courses.

name: Cantaloupe
title: Melon Cantaloupe Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 1.05kg Description: The cantaloupe melon is a rather small and all round sugar melon; with a greenish yellow mesh patterned shell. The pulp is orange colored with juicy and sweet taste.

name: Galia-Melon
title: Galia melon Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 1.01kg Description: Galia melon is a small round sugar melon with a yellowish green; orange; or light brown mesh patterned shell. The pulp is firm and juicy; with a cream white to yellowish green color and a sweet; rich flavor.

name: Honeydew-Melon
title: Honeydew melon Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 1.2kg Description: Honeydew melon is an oval shaped sugarmelon; with a yellow shell. The pulp is creamy light yellow with juicy; sweet and fresh taste; which is milder than other melons.

name: Watermelon
title: Water melon Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 3kg Description: Water melon juicier than sugar melons; and has a round peel with light green base color; with long-tied dark green stripes. The pulp is very juicy; mild and sweet; and occurs with and without kernels.

name: Nectarine
title: Nectarine Class 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 175g Description: The nectarine is a stone fruit with plain peel and yellow or orange pulp; which is somewhat firmer than the peach. Nectarine is suitable for eating naturally but can also be used for pastry; marmalade and jam.

name: Orange
title: Orange Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 280g Description: There are many different types of oranges that ripen and is sold during different parts of the year. The orange is a very important vitamin C source and the vitamins are best kept if the fruit is eaten naturally.

name: Papaya
title: Papaya Class 1
description: Country: Ecuador Description: Papayan has a salmon-pink pulp that is buttery in the texture. The fruit is rich in vitamin A and C.

name: Passion-Fruit
title: Passion fruit Class 1
description: Country: Colombia Description: Passion fruit is a small; round or oval fruit with yellow or dark brownish purple dented shell. Passion fruit's interior consists of many small edible kernels surrounded by succulent pulp. The taste is rich and fresh; and reminiscent of raspberries and orange.

name: Peach
title: Peach Class 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 175g Description: Peach is a stone fruit with yellow or orange pulp and velvety shell. Suitable for eating naturally but can also be used for pastry; marmalade and jam.

name: Anjou
title: Pear Anjou
description: Country and volume: Argentina; ca 170g Description: Anjou pear is a classic pear shaped with rounded stalk with a thin yellowish green shell. The pulp is juicy and has a sweet; nice taste. Anjou is an excellent table fruit that also fits in pastries; then rather unripe.

name: Conference
title: Pear Conference Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 200g Description: Conference is a medium sized pear with long-tapered bottle like shape and a rounded base. To the color; the Conference pear is light greenish yellow with gold brown spots. Pears taste the most when they are really ripe. Suitable for desserts; cheese tray or to eat as it is.

name: Kaiser
title: Pear Bosc-kaiser Class 1
description: Country and volume: Italy; ca 150g Description: The Kaiser Pear is drip-shaped with matte; medium-thick; flaming yellow-brown or brownish shell. The yellowish white pulp is crispy; juicy and sweet; with some fresh acid. Kaiser pears match very well with dessert cheeses and wine; but it is also good to cook; as it retains its shape well.

name: Pineapple
title: Pineapple Klass 1
description: Country: Costa Rica Description: Pineapple fits well to be eaten naturally in for example desserts and fruit salad. Remember to remove the log in the middle.

name: Plum
title: Plum Red Class 1
description: Country and volume: Chile; ca 70g Description: Ripe plums have soft and juicy pulp with sweet taste. Suitable for being eaten naturally; but is also used for preserving and pastries.

name: Pomegranate
title: Pomegranate Klass 1
description: Country and volume: Peru; ca 440g Description: Pomegranate has a sweet; gentle and refreshing taste; making pomegranate suitable for salads and desserts. It is only the kernels of the fruit that you eat. These are taken out by first cutting around the apple without destroying the core. Then turn both halves in opposite directions until they loosen. Finally; the kernels are loosened by knocking a wooden slab on the shell of the half; preferably over a bowl.

name: Red-Grapefruit
title: Grapefruit Red Klass 1
description: Country: Israel Description: The red grapefruit has a red pulp and a slightly pink colored peel. The taste is characteristically bitter; but at the same time fresh and sour. The red grapefruit is sweeter than the blonde grapefruit.

name: Satsumas
title: Satsumas Class 1
description: Country and volume: Spain; ca 100g Description: Satsumas is a sweet and small type of citrus fruit. The fruit is popular as a snack.

name: Asparagus
title: Asparagus Green Class 1
description: Country and volume: Peru; 250g Description: Asparagus has a mild and nice taste and is good as an accessory; as well as a vegetable dishes by itself. Asparagus can be eaten raw; but is usually cooked by boiling in lightly salted water; or grilled. Fresh asparagus is recognized on the stiffness of the stalk; and is preferably stored in refrigerator temperature. The shelf life is maximum one week in the refrigerator; or a couple of days in room temperature.

name: Aubergine
title: Aubergine Class 1
description: Country: Spain Description: Aubergine; or eggplant as it is also called; is usually dark violet. It has a shiny peel and is 15-20 cm long. The pulp is white. Aubergine is always eaten cooked. In addition to Moussaka; Aubergine fits well in pots and gratins.

name: Cabbage
title: Cabbage White Import Class 1
description: Country and volume: Germany; ca 2.8kg Description: White cabbage can be used as a raw food; but it also fits well in for example cabbage rolls; cabbage pudding; cabbage soup; etc.

name: Carrots
title: Carrot Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 170g Description: The orange red color of the carrot comes from the high content of beta carotene; which in the body is converted into vitamin A. Tastefully; carrot is sweet; with a crunchy texture. Carrots can be eaten raw; and are also used in pots; gratins; soups and wok.

name: Cucumber
title: Cucumber Class 1
description: Country: Sweden Description: Fresh cucumber. Fits well in the salad or on the sandwich.

name: Garlic
title: Garlic Class 1
description: Country and volume: China; ca 50g Description: Garlic has unique flavor and smell; and is a good flavoring in pasta dishes; pots; mixes; etc.

name: Ginger
title: Ginger Class 1
description: Country and volume: China; ca 150g Description: Ginger is a herb with a characteristically sharp taste. It is used for flavoring and accessories; especially in Asian cuisine. Vegetables and curries; rice; pickles; meat and fish are good for flavoring with ginger. The rich aroma also fits well with cookies; biscuits; marmalades and sweet desserts.

name: Leek
title: Leek Class 1
description: Country and volume: Sweden; ca 300g Description: Leek has a slightly milder onion flavor and is preferably used for soups and pots; but can also be finely shredded into a salad. It is mainly the white part that is used; although it is fine to eat the green leaves.

name: Brown-Cap-Mushroom
title: Forest mushroom Class 1
description: Country: PolandDescription: The forest mushroom is also called chestnut mushroom; and is a brown mushroom with a fuller flavor than the white mushrooms. It can be eaten raw in for example salads; but are also good to boil; pan-fry or fry.

name: Yellow-Onion
title: Onion Yellow Class 1
description: Country and volume: Sweden; ca 150g Description: Yellow onion is a good flavoring. Fits well both cold and hot in cooking.

name: Green-Bell-Pepper
title: Pepper Green Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 210g Description: There are a variety of colors of peppers. The most common ones are green; yellow; orange; red and white. The paprika always starts as green; but then shifts color when the it becomes more ripe. A green pepper is an unripe and hence a little firmer than the other ones; making it suitable for warm dishes; for example chili con carne; pies; gratin and various pots.

name: Orange-Bell-Pepper
title: Pepper Orange Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 210g Description: The orange pepper is sweeter than the green. It also contains more vitamins and antioxidants than the green. Peppers are good to eat raw in salads and as garnish; but are also good to fry; stew or gratinate; for example with filling. Paprika also fits well in pots; gratins and pies.

name: Red-Bell-Pepper
title: Pepper Red Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 210g Description: The red peppers are much sweeter than the green ones. It also contains more vitamins and antioxidants than the green. Peppers are good to eat raw in salads and as garnish; but are also good to fry; stew or gratinate; for example. with filling. Paprika also fits well in pots; gratins and pies.

name: Yellow-Bell-Pepper
title: Pepper Yellow Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 210g Description: The yellow pepper is much sweeter than the green. It also contains more vitamins and antioxidants than the green. Peppers are good to eat raw in salads and as garnish; but are also good to fry; stew or gratinate; for example with filling. Paprika also fits well in pots; gratins and pies.

name: Floury-Potato
title: Potato Floury Class 1
description: Country: SwedenDescription: Floury potatoes. Extra good for mashed potatoes and to press.

name: Solid-Potato
title: Potato Solid Class 1
description: Country: SwedenDescription: Solid potatoes. A good allround potato that fits well most of the time.

name: Sweet-Potato
title: Sweet potato Class 1
description: Country and volume: USA; ca 360g Description: Sweet potatoes are oblong; irregularly shaped tubers; often slightly larger than regular potatoes. The peel is light brown or red. There are two varieties; one with light pulp and one with yellow orange pulp. Sweet potatoes are used like regular potatoes; but the taste is very different. The sweet potato is very sweet and a bit softer than regular potatoes. It can also be used in desserts; pies and cakes.

name: Red-Beet
title: Red beet Klass 1
description: Country and volume: Sweden; ca 100g Description: Red beets has an earthy and sweet taste and is often eaten on the side; either cooked or preserved; for example; to pölsa; pyttipanna or steak Lindström. It is also common to make Borstj; red beet soup; but the beet can also be shredded as raw food. Red beets are slightly sensitive to heat; frostbites and dehydration and should therefore be kept cool.

name: Beef-Tomato
title: Beef tomato Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 200g Description: An extra large tomato suitable for well for hamburgers and on the grill or in the oven.

name: Regular-Tomato
title: Tomato Class 1
description: Country and volume: Sweden; ca 80g Description: Round and fine tomatoes from Sweden. Rinse and have in the salad or on the sandwich.

name: Vine-Tomato
title: Vine tomato Class 1
description: Country and volume: The Netherlands; ca 140g Description: Round tomatoes with vines in the package. Rinse and have in the salad or on the sandwich.

name: Zucchini
title: Zucchini Class 1
description: Country: Spain Description: Zucchini can be eaten raw; but is usually used in soups; pots; stews; etc.

name: Pumpkin-Spice-Cookies
title: Pumpkin Spice Cookie Treats
description: These delicious cookies are flavored with the seasonal favorite pumpkin spice. Perfect for a spooky Halloween party these cookies offer a warm blend of cinnamon nutmeg and cloves.

name: Bloody-Beet-Dip
title: Vampire Beet Dip
description: This earthy beet dip has a deep red hue making it perfect for a ghoulish gathering. Garlic and lemon add flavor but it's the red beet juice that provides the terrifyingly delightful appearance.

name: Spooky-Guacamole
title: Haunted Avocado Guacamole
description: This guacamole adds a spooky twist to your usual recipe with ghost pepper for extra heat and black olives to resemble spiders. Serve it in a hollowed-out pumpkin for that jack-o-lantern effect.
